    <!-- =====================================================================
         TRANSLATOR / REVIEWER CONTEXT (added for localization QA)

         Every <string>/<plurals> below is preceded by a note stating where it
         appears in the UI (screen / dialog / PDF report / status message) and
         what each placeholder means. Conventions:
           * %1$s, %1$d, %2$d ...: Android positional format arguments filled
             in at runtime. Keep the same number and type as the English; being
             positional, they MAY be reordered within the sentence if the target
             grammar needs it.
           * {name}, {count}: custom SimpleTemplate placeholders (only in
             drink_delete_blocked) — keep the braces and identifiers verbatim.
           * Typographic quote escapes (\u201e \u201c \u201d …): use your locale's
             quotation convention, consistently within the language.
         Comments are documentation only and do not affect the build.
    ===================================================================== -->
